  <div id="bio-text-1st-person">
    <p>
      I am an experimental multimedia artist and creative technologist currently based in New Haven, CT. My practice incorporates electronic media, from analog video and synthesizers to digital systems and code, as well as drawing, print, and liquids. I am especially interested in feedback loops, recursion, self-organizing and emergent structures, and patterns in nature.
    </p>
  
    <p>
      I received an <a href="/mfa/">MFA</a> in Electronic Integrated Arts at Alfred University in 2020, and a BS in Visual Arts and Computer Science from Purchase College in 2014. I have shown work and performed at spaces and events such as Ambient Church (NYC), Eastern Bloc (Montréal), and Ann Arbor Film Festival (Michigan). I have done visiting artist talks and workshops at universities such as CalArts, NYU, and SAIC.
    </p>
