  <h2>
    <img src="https://s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/palomakop.tv/graphics/triangle.svg" class="about-title-graphic" alt=""/> Move Slow and Fix Things
  </h2>

  <p>
    As a practitioner of tech and electronic media, I try to counterbalance the cultural push towards compulsive productivity. I believe that technology should be used to enrich people's lives. Dopamine-draining corporate social media networks, invasive data harvesting, and short-sighted tech bubbles such as cryptocurrency and "artificial intelligence" all serve interests contrary to the long-term well-being of humans and our planet.
  </p>
  <p>
    DIY websites, decentralized networks, and creative communities inspire me to seek another path. A path that moves at a human speed, with space to breathe. One that values careful cultivation over explosive growth, thoughtfulness over conformity.
  </p>

